ADDITIONAL ATTRIBUTION REQUIRED FOR data/geography/
===================================================
A.shp, B.shp and C.shp are derivative works. Area B is the union of
biogeographic provinces 18 (Guatuso-Talamanca) and 19 (Puntarenas-Chiriqui) of
Morrone's (2014) regionalisation, taken from the shapefile of Lowenberg-Neto
(2014); areas A and C are Natural Earth land polygons clipped by B.

If you reuse these polygons you MUST also cite:

  Lowenberg-Neto, P. (2014) Neotropical region: a shapefile of Morrone's (2014)
  biogeographical regionalisation. Zootaxa 3802(2): 300.
  https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3802.2.12
  [Licensed CC BY 3.0. The shapefile's FGDC metadata states access constraints:
   none; use constraints: authorship credit.]

  Morrone, J.J. (2014) Biogeographical regionalisation of the Neotropical
  region. Zootaxa 3782(1): 1-110.
  https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3782.1.1

The land polygons derive from Natural Earth (ne_50m_land v4.0.0), which is in
the public domain and requires no attribution, but whose use we acknowledge.

CC BY 3.0 is not a copyleft licence, so this derivative may carry CC BY 4.0
provided the attribution above is preserved.


